		<title>08Ashurst Church: 2</title>
		<content>{ Margaret Fairless Dowson-}author of  
 'The Roadmender',   (1902)  a classic 
 in the world of 'thoughful'           
 literature. The book was set in the   
 Ashurst area.                         
{The Vamping Horn}- 3 feet long with a 
 7 inch bell, the vamping horn was a   
 church megaphone.  Ashurst's, the     
 smallest of the seven known in        
 England, bears a date of 1770.        
                                       
 The living is in the gift of the      
 Martyr's Memorial Trust and is held in
 plurality with Steyning, the vicar of 
 Steyning being also the rector of     
 Ashurst.                              
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
